import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of size?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.title('What is the relationship between id and size?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=name_counts.index, y=name_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique values in the name field?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
